# Example environment file for deploy/zclassic23.service.
#
# Purpose: keep operator-specific flags (externalip + a seeded addnode
# list) out of the tracked service unit. Copy this template to
#     ~/.config/zclassic23/env
# and edit the values, then `systemctl --user daemon-reload &&
# systemctl --user restart zclassic23` to activate. The service file
# sources this path with `EnvironmentFile=-...`, so if it is missing
# the node still starts — it just falls back to DNS seeds for peer
# discovery and does not advertise a stable external IP.
#
# Variable contract (systemd expands with $VAR, which splits on
# whitespace, so each flag ends up as its own argv element):
#
#   ZCL_EXTERNALIP_FLAG — single -externalip=<ip> flag, or empty.
#                         Use when your node has a stable clearnet IP
#                         you want peers to dial back to.
#
#   ZCL_ADDNODE_FLAGS   — space-separated list of -addnode=<ip[:port]>
#                         flags. These seed the initial peer list
#                         before addrman fills in from gossip.
#
#   ZCL_CHECKPOINT_BUNDLE_SOURCE — path to a two-builder-verified
#                         consensus-state bundle (a
#                         consensus-state-bundle-<height>.sqlite produced by
#                         the canonical exporter, docs/work/CONSENSUS-STATE-
#                         BUNDLE.md) on THIS host. When set, the
#                         ExecStartPre bundle-bootstrap step
#                         (deploy/zclassic23-bundle-bootstrap.sh, docs/
#                         ROM_DELIVERY.md "Local bundle bootstrap") stages a
#                         copy into <datadir>/bundles/ before every start, so
#                         a brand new/empty datadir's zero-flag cold-boot
#                         autodetect finds it with no further operator
#                         action. Leave unset (the common case for a fresh
#                         machine with no bundle of its own yet) and the
#                         step is a silent no-op — the node falls back to
#                         normal sync. Byte delivery only: staging a bundle
#                         here does not trust it — the RECEIPT/
#                         CHECKPOINT_ROM/CHECKPOINT_CONTENT authority at
#                         install time is the only thing that ever does.

ZCL_EXTERNALIP_FLAG=-externalip=205.209.104.118

ZCL_ADDNODE_FLAGS=-addnode=127.0.0.1:8034 -addnode=140.174.189.17 -addnode=140.174.189.3 -addnode=37.187.76.79 -addnode=162.55.92.62 -addnode=157.90.223.151 -addnode=157.173.195.203 -addnode=85.239.232.93 -addnode=154.38.178.121 -addnode=51.178.179.75

# ZCL_CHECKPOINT_BUNDLE_SOURCE=/home/you/zclassic23-bundles/consensus-state-bundle-3056758.sqlite
